    "Background": {
      "text": "Uncommon overall - usually occurs in right liver lobe\nMore abscesses â†’ more severe disease\nHistory of camping is common\nEndemic of Midwest",
      "subsections": {
        "Types": {
          "text": "Pyogenic (80%)\nMost common cause\nAssociated with biliary tract obstruction (most common),\ncholangitis\n,\ndiverticulitis\n, pancreatic abscess,\nappendicitis\nand\ninflammatory bowel disease\n.\nPossible arterial hematogenous seeding:\nsepsis\n, direct\ntrauma\nor instrumentation\nUsually polymicrobial\nAmebic\n(10%)\nE. histolytica most common\nUsually not septic and sick, rarely needs drainage\nFungal\n(<10%),\ncandidal\nHydatid cyst (\nechinococcosis\n)\nAssociated with sheep farmers",
          "tables": []
        }
      },
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
    "Types": {
      "text": "Pyogenic (80%)\nMost common cause\nAssociated with biliary tract obstruction (most common),\ncholangitis\n,\ndiverticulitis\n, pancreatic abscess,\nappendicitis\nand\ninflammatory bowel disease\n.\nPossible arterial hematogenous seeding:\nsepsis\n, direct\ntrauma\nor instrumentation\nUsually polymicrobial\nAmebic\n(10%)\nE. histolytica most common\nUsually not septic and sick, rarely needs drainage\nFungal\n(<10%),\ncandidal\nHydatid cyst (\nechinococcosis\n)\nAssociated with sheep farmers",
